# latex-paper-parallel-assembly — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-04-14)

**Changed by:** Session — Post-assembly citation and verdict cleanup pass (ArchIdeas paper)
**Verification:** verified-local (all four cleanup steps executed end-to-end; paper built cleanly with 0 LaTeX errors after cleanup)

### What changed
- Bumped version from 1.0.0 to 1.1.0
- Added 3 new "When to Use" triggers: removing inline arXiv hrefs, consolidating verdict codes, deduplicating parallel-agent bib stubs
- Added Optional Phase: Post-Assembly Citation and Verdict Cleanup (Steps C1–C4)
  - C1: Remove inline arXiv hrefs (3 patterns: mixed `\href{arxiv}{text\cite{key}}`, bare arXiv ID list items, domain-only links)
  - C2: Consolidate PURSUE/INVESTIGATE/DEPRIORITIZE verdict codes into a single Future Work section; longtable + booktabs package requirements noted
  - C3: Fix `\texttt{}` underscore escaping in research doc pointer lines; `\verb|...|` inside `\textit{}` documented as invalid
  - C4: Deduplicate bib entries from parallel agents; clean rebuild sequence (rm paper.aux paper.bbl paper.blg → pdflatex → bibtex → pdflatex → pdflatex)
- Added 4 new Failed Attempts rows: `\verb` inside `\textit{}`, Python str.replace double-escape, fixing bib duplicates without clearing .aux, replacing verdict codes globally
- Added Verified Citation and Verdict Cleanup (2026-04-14) table to Results & Parameters
- Added Clean Bib Rebuild Sequence (copy-paste) to Results & Parameters
- Added ArchIdeas post-assembly cleanup row to Verified On table
- Updated tags: added cleanup, citations, verdicts
- Updated description to include the 3 new post-assembly cleanup use cases

### Why
After assembling the ArchIdeas 38-idea LaTeX paper from 4 parallel agents, a major post-assembly cleanup pass revealed four distinct recurring issues: (1) parallel agents added inline `\href{https://arxiv.org/abs/...}{...}` wrappers around citation text that needed stripping, (2) verdict codes PURSUE/INVESTIGATE/DEPRIORITIZE were scattered across body paragraphs and table rows rather than consolidated in a dedicated Future Work section, (3) agents writing research doc pointers used `\texttt{research_X_Y_*.md}` with unescaped underscores causing "Missing $ inserted" LaTeX errors, and (4) parallel merge agents introduced uppercase cite key duplicates (e.g., `Banino2021PonderNet`) clashing with lowercase originals (`banino2021pondernet`) — bibtex reported "Case mismatch" and "Repeated entry" errors that persisted until the .aux file was cleared.

### Previous version (v1.0.0) snapshot

Key v1.0.0 content before this amendment:

```markdown
date: 2026-04-14
version: 1.0.0
tags: [latex, parallel, assembly, pdflatex, bibtex]

## When to Use
- A single agent cannot write the full paper without hitting context limits (>50 ideas, >40 pages)
- You have independent parallel-writable sections
- You need a reproducible farm-and-assemble pattern with explicit error-remediation steps
- Post-assembly compilation fails due to Unicode, missing bib keys, \citeauthor, or tabular column drift

